    </introduction>
    


    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-speed-in-kilometre-per-hour-to-metres-per-second">
      <title>Converting speed in kilometre per hour<m>(km/h)</m> to metres per second<m>(m/s)</m>.</title>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{green} \text{Work in groups}}</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        Read the story below.
      </p>
      <p>
        Juma is a school driver. He drives carfully and observes all the traffic rules.
        One day, he took learners for on educatianal trip. He drove at a speed of <m>60\,km/hr</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Why is it important to observe traffic rules?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>How many kilometres did the bus cover in <m>1</m> hour?</li>
          <li>What was the speed of the bus in <m>m/s</m>?</li>
          <li>Share your work with other learners in class.</li>
            
        </ol>
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{blue} \text{Learning point.}}</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        To convert speed speed in kilometre per hour to metres per second, you 
        convert the distance to metres and one hour to seconds, then devide.
      </p>

      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A car travelled a distance of <m>180\,km</m> in <m>2</m> hours. 
            What was the speed of the car in <m>m/s</m>?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <sidebyside>
            <p>
              <md>
                <mrow>\text{If} \, 1\,km= \amp 1\,000\,m </mrow>
                <mrow> 180\,km=\amp 180 \times 1\,000\,m </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp {\color{green} 180\,000\,m}</mrow>
                <mrow> \text{If} \,1\,hour=\amp 3\,600 \, seconds </mrow>
                <mrow> 2\, hours=\amp 2 \times  3\,600 \, seconds </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp {\color{green} 7\,200\, seconds } </mrow>
                <mrow> \text{Speed} =\amp \frac{Distance\,covered}{time\,taken} </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp (\frac{{\color{green} 180\,000}}{{\color{green} 7\,200}})\,m/s </mrow>
                <mrow> =\amp {\color{blue} 25\,m/s}</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>
            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium" >
              <row>
                <cell>a) Convert the distance from kilometres to metre.</cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>b) Convert the time from hours to second.</cell>
              </row>
              <row bottom="medium">
                <cell>c) Devide the distance in metres by the time in seconds.</cell>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </sidebyside>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-speed-in-metres-per-second-to-kilometres-per-hour">
      <title>Converting speed in metres per second<m>(m/s)</m> to kilometres per hour<m>km/h</m></title>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{green} \text{Work in groups}}</m>
      </p>
      <sidebyside>
        
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                The picture alongside shows an ambulence. The ambulence transported 
                a sick person to Matibabu Hospital, <m>72\,000\,m</m> away.The journey took <m>40</m> minutes. 
                Calculate the speed of the ambulence in metres per second.
              </p>
              
            </li>
            <li>Work out the distance, in kilometres, that the ambulence 
            coveredin one second.</li>
            <li>How many kilometres did the ambulence  cover in one hour?</li>
            <li>What was the speed of the ambulence in kilometres per hour?</li>
            <li>Share your work with other learners in class. </li>

          </ol>
        </p>
        <image source="/Hospital.png" >
          <shortdescription></shortdescription>
        </image>
      </sidebyside>
      <p>
        <m>{\color{blue} \text{Learning point.}}</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        To convert speed in metres per second to kilometres per hour, you 
        convert the distance to kilometres and the one second to hours, then divide.
      </p>

      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            In a swimming competition, the fastest swimmer took <m>25</m> second 
            to complete a <m>62.5\, m</m> race. Calculate the speed of the swimmer in kilometres per hour 
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            First,
          </p>
          <p>
            Convert <m>62.5\, m</m> to kilometres.
          </p>
          <p>
            Convert <m>25\, s</m> to hours.
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> \text{If} \,1\,000=\amp 1\,km</mrow>
              <mrow> 62.5\,m=\amp \frac{62.5}{1\,000}\,km </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{16}\,km</mrow>
              <mrow> \text{If}\,3\,600\,s=\amp 1\,h </mrow>
              <mrow> 25\,s =\amp \frac{25}{3\,600}\,h  </mrow>
              <mrow>\text{Speed} = \amp \text{distance} \div \text{time} </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{16}\,km \div \frac{25}{3\,600}\,h </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{16}\,km \times \frac{3\,600}{25}\,h</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp {\color{blue} 9\,km/h} </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    
    
